<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="prepared-adj">prepared <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /prɪ'peəd/    美 /prɪ'perd/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>准备好的；有所准备的：</strong></h4>
<p>反 unprepared </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Our monitor presented our teacher with the prepared flowers.
我们班长给老师献上了准备好的花。</p><footer>2012 陕西书面表达</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It seems you’re <strong>well prepared</strong>. 
看来你做好了充分的准备。</p><footer>2008 重庆</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>be / get prepared for:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We should improve our study methods and get well prepared for examinations. 
我们应该改进学习方法，为考试做好充分准备。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>be / get prepared to do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>All the competitors must <strong>be fully prepared to</strong> give the best performance.
所有参赛者一定要做好充分准备，以便发挥最佳水平。</p><footer>2009 天津书面表达改</footer></div></div>